Name: Archbold Biological Station
Description: Protects the largest undisturbed tract of the Lake Wales Ridge

Name: Big Cypress Bend
Description: A part of Fakahatchee Strand Preserve State Park , it features the largest grove of royal palm trees in the country

Name: Corkscrew Swamp Sanctuary
Description: Contains the nation 's largest remaining virgin strand of bald cypress trees

Name: Devil 's Millhopper
Description: A karst dry sinkhole located within the eponymous state park

Name: Emeralda Marsh
Description: This inland freshwater sawgrass marsh is also a popular birding area

Name: Florida Caverns Natural Area
Description: Eponymous state park protects Florida 's only publicly accessible cave . Winter home of the endangered Indiana bat

Name: Ichetucknee Springs
Description: Artisan spring , the state 's third largest , included in eponymous state park

Name: Lignumvitae Key
Description: Located in an eponymous state park , contains the best preserved tropical hammock forest in the country

Name: Manatee Springs
Description: An eponymous state park surrounds the state 's sixth largest artisan spring

Name: Osceola Research Natural Area
Description: Isolated mixed hardwood forest featuring virgin bald cypress strands . A portion of Osceola National Forest

Name: Paynes Prairie
Description: Freshwater marsh in one of the state 's largest sinks . Majority of the site included in Paynes Prairie Preserve State Park

Name: Rainbow Springs
Description: Florida 's second largest artisan spring . Part of an eponymous state park

Name: Reed Wilderness Seashore Sanctuary
Description: A part of Hobe Sound National Wildlife Refuge , protects the largest undisturbed stretch of Florida 's Atlantic coast . A nesting site of the loggerhead turtle

Name: San Felasco Hammock
Description: Mainly located in San Felasco Hammock Preserve State Park , contains a diverse forest environment

Name: Silver Springs
Description: Eponymous state park surrounds the state 's largest artesian spring

Name: Torreya State Park
Description: Steep ravines cut through this eponymous state park . Home of endangered plants such as the Florida yew

Name: Waccasassa Bay Preserve State Park
Description: Brackish mangrove protected in an eponymous state park

Name: Wakulla Springs
Description: Located in Edward Ball Wakulla Springs State Park , includes the state 's deepest artesian spring
